==Dharuk==
===Other spellings===
*[[deein]]
===Etymology===
''Dyin'' was loaned into English as '''[[gin#Etymology 3|gin]]'''.
===Noun===
'''dyin'''

# [[woman]]
===Quotations===
*'''1793''', [[w:Watkin Tench|Watkin Tench]], ''A Complete Account of the Settlement at Port Jackson''
*:The letter ‘y’ frequently follows ‘d’ in the same syllable. Thus the word which signifies a woman is ‘'''dyin'''’; although the structure of our language requires us to spell it ‘'''deein'''’.
